        "cooked": "<p>Even if you mute a chat permanently, new messages there will still add to the badge count, both within the app and on the app icon itself. This is a problem for busy groups where I want to be able to view stuff there, but I don‚Äôt need to keep up with every post.</p>\n<p>iOS and Desktop both have this feature (called ‚ÄúCount Muted Conversations‚Äù in the <a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/360043273491-In-App-Notification-Options#ios_notification_options\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">support docs</a>, ‚ÄúInclude Muted Chats‚Äù on current iOS devices, and ‚ÄúInclude muted chats in badge count‚Äù on Desktop).</p>\n<p>So why can‚Äôt Android get this (seemingly) simple but important QoL feature?</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/5/7550904dae0a5fa21e4065af34dc1999990674e1.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/7550904dae0a5fa21e4065af34dc1999990674e1\" title=\"signal-2026-01-26-135140\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/5/7550904dae0a5fa21e4065af34dc1999990674e1_2_251x500.jpeg\" alt=\"signal-2026-01-26-135140\" data-base62-sha1=\"gJOtciIMKnc3SzDOEkImPRQYqoF\" width=\"251\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/5/7550904dae0a5fa21e4065af34dc1999990674e1_2_251x500.jpeg, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/5/7550904dae0a5fa21e4065af34dc1999990674e1_2_376x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/7/5/7550904dae0a5fa21e4065af34dc1999990674e1_2_502x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"2A2A2C\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">signal-2026-01-26-135140</span><span class=\"informations\">1029√ó2048 114 KB</span><svg 